#!/bin/ratpoison equivalent.

See also BangPatch http://ratpoison.wxcvbn.org/cgi-bin/wiki.pl/BangPatch

See also contrib/rpbatch.pl in the source package.

Putting #!/usr/bin/ratpoison at the start of a ratpoison script does not work, because ratpoison does not examine stdin. This is an alternative:

FH is a pseudo-unique filename based on time, process ID and user ID. There may be a better way to get unique filenames on your system.

by twb
